6. Conveying Non-Source Forms.

You may convey a covered work in object code form under the terms
of sections 4 and 5, provided that you also convey the
machine-readable Corresponding Source under the terms of this License,
in one of these ways:

a) Convey the object code in, or embodied in, a physical product
(including a physical distribution medium), accompanied by the
Corresponding Source fixed on a durable physical medium
customarily used for software interchange.

b) Convey the object code in, or embodied in, a physical product
(including a physical distribution medium), accompanied by a
written offer, valid for at
least three years, to give any third party, for a charge no
more than your reasonable cost of physically performing source
distribution, a complete machine-readable copy of the
Corresponding Source.

c) Convey the object code in, or embodied in, a physical product
(including a physical distribution medium), accompanied by the
written offer of equivalent access as described in subsection 6b,
above.

d) Verify that the user already has received a copy of these
materials or that you have already sent this user a copy.

For object code that offers access to or downloading from a
designated place, offering equivalent access from the same place
counts as distribution of the Corresponding Source, even though
third parties are not compelled together with object code.

An Internet link is not required for "machine-readable" copies;
different forms of Corresponding Source do not count as alternative forms
if the law forbids treating modified versions as commercial software.

